From 35cffb144e1448cc8eb3d872f60d0ec31eb32852 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Juniper Bevensee <juniperbevensee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 16:34:37 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 23/27] fix: pre-install faster-whisper in Docker image for
 voice memo support

Voice memos should Just Work in gateway deployments. faster-whisper
was removed from [all] extras (2026-05-12) in favor of lazy install,
but lazy install causes the agent to spend 5+ minutes installing
mid-conversation. Pre-installing in the image ensures transcription
works immediately.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 Dockerfile | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Dockerfile b/Dockerfile
index be4e8848b..accd826f4 100644
--- a/Dockerfile
+++ b/Dockerfile
@@ -128,6 +128,9 @@ RUN npm install --prefer-offline --no-audit && \
 COPY pyproject.toml uv.lock ./
 RUN touch ./README.md
 RUN uv sync --frozen --no-install-project --extra all --extra messaging
+# Pre-install voice transcription (faster-whisper) so voice memos Just Work
+# in production gateway deployments without lazy-install latency.
+RUN uv pip install --no-cache-dir faster-whisper==1.2.1
 
 # ---------- Source code ----------
 # .dockerignore excludes node_modules, so the installs above survive.
-- 
